This paper deals with the encoding of a function represented with a smooth decomposable negation normal form (DNNF), which is a common representation used in artificial intelligence and knowledge representation. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves logical reasoning and constraint satisfaction, which suggests cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with propositional logic and conjunctive normal form (CNF), which are topics covered in cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
